Citations
Date:  12/11/1902
Source:  Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:  74
Edition:
Quote:  The fleece-picker takes the fleece by the hind legs, and gathers it towards him; takes it to the rolling table, and throws it out with the outside of the fleece upwards; the roller skirts it, rolls it up tightly, and hands it to the classer, who puts the fleece in the proper bin.
